HSA Receipt Processor (Rust Worker)
A high-performance, asynchronous background worker built in Rust to handle medical receipt OCR processing. This worker acts as the "Core" processing engine for the ActualBridge HSA management ecosystem.

🏗 Architecture
This project follows a Hybrid Cloud pattern, leveraging the strengths of two distinct ecosystems:

Edge (C# / .NET): Handles user authentication, API management, and the web frontend.

Core (Rust): A stateless, high-concurrency worker that manages the resource-intensive OCR pipeline and data integrity.

The "Durable" Processing Loop
The worker implements an explicit Asynchronous HTTP Polling pattern to interact with Azure AI Services:

Ingest: Polls an Azure Storage Queue for new receipt processing requests.

Download: Retrieves the raw receipt bytes from Azure Blob Storage into memory.

Analyze: Submits the data to Azure Document Intelligence (Prebuilt-Receipt Model).

Poll: Executes a non-blocking retry loop to monitor AI analysis status (mimicking a Durable Function orchestration).

Enrich: Updates the original Blob metadata with extracted Vendor, Amount, Service Date, and Confidence scores.

Finalize: Deletes the queue message upon successful completion.

🚀 Key Features
Memory Efficient: Processes image bytes entirely in-memory to minimize I/O overhead.

Type-Safe OCR: Uses a custom OcrEngine trait, allowing for seamless swapping between Azure AI and local engines (like Tesseract).

Resilient Metadata: Aligns with C# MedicalReceipt schemas, ensuring the Blob Storage remains a searchable "Source of Truth."

Fully Mocked Suite: Unit tests utilize mockito to simulate complex Azure AI lifecycles without incurring cloud costs.

🛠 Tech Stack
Language: Rust (Latest Stable)

Async Runtime: tokio

Cloud SDKs: azure_storage_blobs, azure_storage_queues

HTTP Client: reqwest (REST API integration)

Serialization: serde, serde_json

🚦 Getting Started
Prerequisites
Rust toolchain installed.

An Azure Storage Account and Document Intelligence resource.

Environment Variables
Create a .env file or export the following:

Bash
STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING="DefaultEndpointsProtocol=https;AccountName=...;AccountKey=..."
DOC_INTEL_ENDPOINT="https://your-resource.cognitiveservices.azure.com/"
DOC_INTEL_KEY="your-api-key"

Running the Worker
cargo run --release

Running Tests
cargo test